cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.NI 

This paper deals with distributed coordination and optimization in power networks, which involves the intersection of several computer science subfields. The most likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper focuses on designing coordination schemes for power networks. The second likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper discusses the bandwidth requirements for two-way communication schemes and proposes a one-way communication scheme. The third likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper employs a dual descent distributed optimization algorithm. The fourth likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper deals with distributed coordination and optimization. The fifth likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper discusses communication requirements and proposes a one-way communication scheme.
